<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-o7lvc-QHtPN9bx_elYizww" name=",_QHkpkL-JEd2e1-cAeXIm5A" guid="-o7lvc-QHtPN9bx_elYizww" changeDate="2008-12-01T10:38:55.455+0100">
  <mainDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The results of all the projects are analysed, gathering all the available information to extract the best practices and useful policies. This will help to improve the result of incoming projects. The final result of this task is the knowledge base updated with new Enterprise Service Architecture (ESA) and Enterprise Realisation Architecture (ERA) models, including used and recommended policies. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Note: This task is very important for large enterprises which have many projects and would obtain many benefits reusing solutions from previous projects. Other types of enterprises will also obtain benefits, but it is not so critical for them.&lt;/SPAN></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgMsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Create infrastructure support " guid="_UBUgMsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>If the enterprise has no experience in services integration or it does not maintain any knowledge base, the first step should be to analyse how to create the adequate infrastructure to support a knowledge base which will be used in later projects. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgMMHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Access knowledge base data structure " guid="_UBUgMMHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Once the knowledge base is working, the next step will be to access it to learn how previous projects data are stored. This is important to understand the structure of the information. The information which will be stored later will have to follow that structure. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgMcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Gather projects information and analyze it " guid="_UBUgMcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Next step is to gather information about recent projects to complete the information contained in the knowledge base. After gathering all de data available, analyze the solutions to extract patterns, policies, composition designs, conclusions, lessons learnt, good practices... &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>In the case there is no previous projects or just a few ones, it is recommended to carry out a research about possible approaches to solve composition problems. The research result might be the base of a knowledge base. After this research, analyse all the data and extract which good practices, patterns, policies… will be applicable for the problem domain. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgM8HrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Package information and complete the analysis (For projects without ESA and/or ERA) " guid="_UBUgM8HrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>First, Enterprise Service Architecture (ESA) and Enterprise Realisation Architecture (ERA )models will be obtained, packaging all the information about the solutions provided in other projects, case studies, examples… These will be complete solution packages to be reused. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Then, ESA and ERA will be analyzed in such a way that architecture patterns and policies (to explain how to use them) will be developed or updated (if they were part of a knowledge base). This information will be also packed with good practices, conclusions and lessons learnt.&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN>&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>“Define service sourcing policy” technique might help to analyse if decisions taken about services provisioning were adequate or should be changed in later projects. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgL8HrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Store information to be used later " guid="_UBUgL8HrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT size=3>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The later step is store all the information in a place where it will be accessible by anyone who needs it. The structure of the data should be good enough to store all the useful information in a clear way. A good way to arrange all the data might be by application domain. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>This&#xD;
task is necessary to maintain the infrastructure which will support development teams during new projects.&lt;/span></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
